<h2 id="common-reminders">Common Reminders</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Always use the `+-` patch format in code returns to prevent overwriting existing functions.</li>
    <li>Update documentation after making changes to the code.</li>
    <li>Commit changes regularly with meaningful messages.</li>
    <li>Ensure all navigation links within each sub-document are unique.</li>
    <li>Ensure that all URLs referenced in the application have corresponding routes defined in controllers to avoid 404 errors.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="example-prompt">Example Prompt</h2>
<p>When reminding the assistant, you can say: "Please follow the guidelines outlined in guidelines.tt, especially regarding the `+-` patch format for code returns and the prohibition on using placeholders in code returns."</p>

